                  <p align="left"
                  <p>IPRA's Facility Management Section encompasses members involved 
                    with administration, supervision, maintenance and/or programming 
                    of ice rinks, golf courses, swimming pools, racquet, fitness 
                    or community centers, zoos, farms, museums, nature centers 
                    and other recreation or revenue facilities in Illinois.</p>
                  <p><b>You're Invited...</b><br>
                    Here is your chance to get involved with IPRA Facility Section. 
                    Becoming an active member by attending monthly meetings will 
                    give you a chance to network with other professionals who 
                    deal with the same day to day problems, concerns, and demands 
                    that you do.</p>
                  <p>This is a great way to get new ideas and meet a lot of new 
                    people who may be able to help you as your career progresses 
                    in the field.</p>
					<p align="center"><strong>2005 Facility Management Section Award Winners</strong></p>
<p>The winners of the 2005 Facility Management Awards were presented with their awards at the Annual Facility Management and Recreation Sections Joint Meeting and Luncheon at the Bartlett Park District on November 4, 2005.  Congratulations winners!</p>
<p align="center"><img src="/images/facmgmtaward2005.jpg" border="0"></p>
<p><strong>Bottom Row (Left to Right)</strong><br>
Manager of the Year – Aquatics – Fred Gusel,
Director’s Award – Tom Bower – Winfield Park District</p>
<p><strong>Top Row (Left to Right)</strong><br>
Manager of the Year – Community Centers – Sandy Harris – Schaumburg Park District,
Manager of the Year – Natural Museums - Becky Lambert – Oak Brook Terrace Park District,
Manager of the Year – Fitness - Laura Marquardt – Wheaton Park District,
Young Professional of the Year – Kim Wascher – City of South Elgin Park & Recreation Department,
Professional of the Year – Carrie Haupert – Wheaton Park District</p>



